      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Why do you suppose ketone halogenations in acidic media are referred to as being acid-<i>catalyzed</i>, whereas halogenations in basic media are base-<i>promoted</i>? In other words, why is a full equivalent of base required for halogenation?",
